WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:00.920
[MUSIC - THEME SONG]
- Let's go!

00:00.920 --> 00:01.830
(SINGING) Peter Rabbit,

00:01.830 --> 00:05.660
Go on a run for our lives,

00:05.660 --> 00:08.790
We'll tear a hole in
every fence and every wall.

00:08.790 --> 00:09.690
Peter Rabbit.

00:09.690 --> 00:13.380
Run through the fields,
run wild and free,

00:13.380 --> 00:16.640
And grab a piece of
every radish that we see.

00:16.640 --> 00:17.340
Peter Rabbit.

00:17.340 --> 00:20.560
Go day and night, go for it all.

00:20.560 --> 00:23.530
It's time to fly, come on,
the wind's begun to blow.

00:23.530 --> 00:24.520
Let's go!

00:24.520 --> 00:27.280
Just you and I, we weren't
made for going slow.

00:27.280 --> 00:27.980
Let's go!

00:27.980 --> 00:30.750
Adventure calls again,
it's our command.

00:30.750 --> 00:31.450
Let's go!

00:31.450 --> 00:32.439
Peter Rabbit,

00:32.439 --> 00:33.420
Let's go!

00:33.420 --> 00:34.420
Peter Rabbit,

00:34.420 --> 00:35.900
Let's go!

00:35.900 --> 00:37.390
Peter Rabbit, let's go!

00:41.350 --> 00:43.730
NARRATOR: The Tale
of the Grumpy Owl.

00:53.630 --> 01:00.070
OWL: (HOOTING) Woo hoo!

01:18.380 --> 01:20.620
LILY BOBTAIL: Uh,
Peter, why don't you

01:20.620 --> 01:22.370
just tell us what
you're looking for

01:22.370 --> 01:23.830
and then we can
help you find it?

01:27.200 --> 01:29.440
Uh, uh, Peter?

01:33.160 --> 01:36.450
Ah-ha!

01:36.450 --> 01:38.330
Look out!

01:38.330 --> 01:40.680
Whoa!

01:40.680 --> 01:43.370
Hey, careful!

01:43.370 --> 01:44.960
Ha ha.

01:44.960 --> 01:45.850
Oof!

01:45.850 --> 01:47.259
It's my journal.

01:47.259 --> 01:49.220
I can't find it anywhere!

01:49.220 --> 01:50.030
Journal?

01:50.030 --> 01:51.550
You know, the journal.

01:51.550 --> 01:55.190
The one my dad left for me!

01:55.190 --> 01:55.890
Ow.

01:55.890 --> 01:57.009
OK.

01:57.009 --> 01:58.870
You've got to think logically.

01:58.870 --> 02:00.310
When did you last see it?

02:00.310 --> 02:03.160
I was reading it
in bed last night.

02:03.160 --> 02:06.100
Then I was dreaming,
and then I heard a hoot.

02:06.100 --> 02:08.630
And then-- of course!

02:08.630 --> 02:09.620
Oh, ow!

02:12.590 --> 02:14.070
Uh, Peter?

02:25.920 --> 02:28.200
Old Brown stole my journal!

02:30.970 --> 02:32.250
I've got to get it back!

02:32.250 --> 02:34.470
I'll help you.

02:34.470 --> 02:37.480
Uh, ah, whoa!

02:37.480 --> 02:38.770
Me too.

02:38.770 --> 02:39.720
Ha!

02:44.450 --> 02:45.970
Owl Island, here I come!

02:48.860 --> 02:50.690
Wait, Peter!

02:50.690 --> 02:53.520
Owl Island is half a mile away.

02:53.520 --> 02:55.560
I know that for a fact.

02:55.560 --> 02:58.690
We can't swim that far.

02:58.690 --> 03:00.450
But I've got to
get over there!

03:00.450 --> 03:02.670
What we need is a boat.

03:02.670 --> 03:03.780
Yes.

03:03.780 --> 03:05.190
We could build one.

03:05.190 --> 03:07.320
The plans are in
my dad's journal!

03:07.320 --> 03:08.580
Oh.

03:08.580 --> 03:12.090
This is exactly why we
need to get it back.

03:12.090 --> 03:14.880
Maybe the squirrels
can help us.

03:14.880 --> 03:17.010
Squirrels don't
have boats, Benjamin.

03:17.010 --> 03:20.930
No, but they have rafts.

03:20.930 --> 03:24.190
[SQUIRRELS CHATTERING AND
LAUGHING]

03:26.520 --> 03:28.040
I've got this.

03:28.040 --> 03:30.650
Ears, Benjamin.

03:30.650 --> 03:32.540
[SHRILL WHISTLING]

03:33.950 --> 03:36.420
That's got their attention.

03:36.420 --> 03:39.590
[SQUIRRELS CHATTERING AND
LAUGHING]

03:39.590 --> 03:40.720
Thanks for the lift, Nutkin.

03:40.720 --> 03:43.400
(WHISPERING) I'm not Nutkin.

03:43.400 --> 03:45.300
Uh, you're not?

03:45.300 --> 03:48.270
(STAGE WHISPERING)
I'm not even a squirrel!

03:48.270 --> 03:49.740
And neither are my friends.

03:49.740 --> 03:51.730
[SQUIRRELS CHATTERING]

04:00.200 --> 04:01.210
Psst.

04:01.210 --> 04:02.200
Hey guys.

04:02.200 --> 04:06.940
It's me, Nutkin! (LAUGHS)
Great disguise, huh?

04:06.940 --> 04:08.120
Brilliant.

04:08.120 --> 04:09.770
We would have never
guessed you were squirrels.

04:09.770 --> 04:12.100
We run a top-secret mission.

04:12.100 --> 04:13.650
All very hush-hush!

04:13.650 --> 04:14.770
Us, too.

04:14.770 --> 04:17.529
Watch out for that
grumpy owl, then.

04:17.529 --> 04:21.519
He hates visitors,
especially squirrels!

04:24.890 --> 04:25.860
[GASPING]

04:25.860 --> 04:29.570
Um, uh, how does he
feel about rabbits?

04:29.570 --> 04:32.200
Old Brown's not crazy
about them, either.

04:32.200 --> 04:33.620
Bye!

04:33.620 --> 04:35.080
Come on.

04:35.080 --> 04:35.970
Let's hop to it!

04:45.510 --> 04:48.020
Don't worry, Benjamin.

04:48.020 --> 04:51.830
As long as we don't wake
Old Brown up, we'll be OK.

04:51.830 --> 04:53.710
Just keep quiet.

04:53.710 --> 04:55.340
Quiet.

04:55.340 --> 04:58.930
Sure, I can do that.

04:58.930 --> 04:59.900
Ah.

04:59.900 --> 05:02.200
Ah.

05:02.200 --> 05:03.550
Oh, ah.

05:03.550 --> 05:04.460
Oh, ah.

05:04.460 --> 05:05.520
Ouch!

05:05.520 --> 05:06.370
Uh, sorry.

05:15.390 --> 05:16.350
There it is.

05:16.350 --> 05:17.050
Dad's journal.

05:22.660 --> 05:26.050
Whoa, whoa!

05:26.050 --> 05:28.740
I've got a better idea.

05:28.740 --> 05:32.390
It's a hazelnut catapult. We
can knock the journal down.

05:38.370 --> 05:39.200
OK.

05:39.200 --> 05:40.470
Here we go.

05:40.470 --> 05:42.230
1, 2--

05:42.230 --> 05:42.940
Don't miss.

05:42.940 --> 05:44.040
OK, Peter?

05:44.040 --> 05:46.260
Yes, thanks.

05:46.260 --> 05:47.860
1, 2--

05:47.860 --> 05:50.700
And you don't want to
wake Old Brown, do you?

05:50.700 --> 05:52.540
Yes, I know.

05:52.540 --> 05:54.360
Stop interrupting!

05:54.360 --> 05:55.720
1, 2--

05:55.720 --> 05:58.790
Do you want to take
a practise shot first?

05:58.790 --> 06:00.240
Whoa, whoa!

06:00.240 --> 06:02.180
[HOOTING]

06:09.460 --> 06:10.910
[SNORING]

06:10.910 --> 06:12.020
Sorry.

06:12.020 --> 06:13.430
It's OK.

06:13.430 --> 06:14.960
Let's go find some
more hazelnuts.

06:21.370 --> 06:23.220
Nutkin?

06:23.220 --> 06:25.720
(WHISPERING) I'm not here.

06:25.720 --> 06:26.550
[CHATTERING]

06:26.550 --> 06:29.520
So, your secret
mission was stealing all

06:29.520 --> 06:31.920
of Old Brown's hazelnuts, huh?

06:31.920 --> 06:33.500
Who told you?

06:33.500 --> 06:34.680
Was it Felix?

06:34.680 --> 06:35.850
I bet it was.

06:35.850 --> 06:37.560
Oh, he's such a blabbermouth!

06:37.560 --> 06:39.409
[INDIGNANT CHATTERING]

06:40.330 --> 06:43.500
We're here to get
Peter's journal back.

06:43.500 --> 06:44.730
Old Brown stole It.

06:44.730 --> 06:47.909
That grumpy old owl
stole your journal?

06:47.909 --> 06:51.730
I have had it with him!

06:51.730 --> 06:54.370
Old Brown has been an
enemy of the squirrel tribe

06:54.370 --> 06:56.110
for generations!

06:56.110 --> 07:02.010
First, he steals my tail, and
now he steals your journal?

07:02.010 --> 07:04.320
We've got to do something!

07:04.320 --> 07:09.630
Squirrel Tribe, to battle!

07:09.630 --> 07:11.590
[CHATTERING]

07:13.070 --> 07:14.030
OK.

07:14.030 --> 07:16.340
I'll do it myself.

07:16.340 --> 07:17.140
Come on.

07:21.530 --> 07:24.190
Nutkin, really, you
don't have to do this.

07:24.190 --> 07:25.900
It's my problem.

07:25.900 --> 07:27.100
You want your journal back?

07:27.100 --> 07:30.730
You'll have it back!

07:30.730 --> 07:40.990
The secret is to be fast,
sneaky, and very, very quiet.

07:40.990 --> 07:41.950
Woo-hoo!

07:41.950 --> 07:44.310
Ha, ha, ha, see?

07:44.310 --> 07:45.320
I did it!

07:45.320 --> 07:46.300
No!

07:46.300 --> 07:48.450
Look out, Nutkin!

07:48.450 --> 07:49.790
What?

07:49.790 --> 07:51.620
You want more dancing?

07:51.620 --> 07:52.620
OK!

07:52.620 --> 07:53.620
[GROWLING]

07:54.620 --> 07:57.159
Old Brown has Nutkin!

07:57.159 --> 07:58.870
We have to help him!

07:58.870 --> 07:59.730
But how?

08:03.850 --> 08:06.730
Come on!

08:06.730 --> 08:10.080
1, 2, 3!

08:10.080 --> 08:11.790
Whoa!

08:11.790 --> 08:13.990
He needs a crash mat!

08:13.990 --> 08:14.690
Ah!

08:14.690 --> 08:17.150
Tell me when it's over!

08:17.150 --> 08:20.720
How many times have
I told you, Nutkin?

08:20.720 --> 08:24.820
Never, ever wake up an owl!

08:24.820 --> 08:26.140
I'm not Nutkin.

08:26.140 --> 08:27.550
Ha, ha!

08:27.550 --> 08:30.090
You silly squirrel.

08:30.090 --> 08:33.500
One would have hoped you've
learned your lesson by now.

08:33.500 --> 08:35.230
Stay away from my friend!

08:35.230 --> 08:37.360
Oh, but I wasn't even, uh--

08:37.360 --> 08:38.059
Uh.

08:38.059 --> 08:39.140
Oh, oh!

08:39.140 --> 08:41.140
Oh, you were talking to him,
weren't you? (LAUGHS NERVOUSLY)

08:41.140 --> 08:42.150
Carry on.

08:42.150 --> 08:45.160
Peter Rabbit, up a tree?

08:45.160 --> 08:46.420
Whatever next?

08:46.420 --> 08:50.490
You let Nutkin go, and give
me back my dad's journal, too!

08:50.490 --> 08:52.390
Heh, heh, heh, heh.

08:52.390 --> 08:53.380
So.

08:53.380 --> 08:55.620
You want your book, do you?

08:55.620 --> 08:57.120
It was my dad's.

08:57.120 --> 08:57.820
Give it back!

08:57.820 --> 08:59.440
Heh, heh, heh.

08:59.440 --> 09:01.080
You know what they say.

09:01.080 --> 09:02.730
Keepers, finders.

09:02.730 --> 09:04.810
Uh, I think you mean
"finders, keepers."

09:04.810 --> 09:05.730
Hm?

09:05.730 --> 09:07.410
Tailfeathers!

09:07.410 --> 09:08.570
Oh! (WHIMPERS)

09:08.570 --> 09:10.480
I'll make you a deal.

09:10.480 --> 09:17.090
You can have Nutkin back, or
your precious journal, but not

09:17.090 --> 09:18.360
both.

09:18.360 --> 09:19.910
Your choice, Peter.

09:23.020 --> 09:23.720
[WHIMPERING]

09:23.720 --> 09:24.700
Well?

09:24.700 --> 09:26.240
I'm sorry to do this, dad.

09:29.660 --> 09:32.510
BOTH: Whoa!

09:32.510 --> 09:33.210
Wow!

09:33.210 --> 09:35.260
Oh, crash mat!

09:35.260 --> 09:37.190
Great idea.

09:37.190 --> 09:39.020
You rabbits are so smart.

09:39.020 --> 09:43.400
But if that's the crash
mat, then what did we--

09:43.400 --> 09:44.450
Benjamin!

09:44.450 --> 09:45.350
Ah.

09:45.350 --> 09:47.240
You're welcome.

09:47.240 --> 09:48.560
Back to the raft.

09:48.560 --> 09:49.660
Let's hop to it!

09:49.660 --> 09:52.510
But Peter, what
about your journal?

09:52.510 --> 09:53.700
I know.

09:53.700 --> 09:56.810
I'm going to miss it, but some
things are more important.

09:56.810 --> 10:03.370
(WAILING) Oh, that's
just so sweet of you!

10:03.370 --> 10:04.070
No, really.

10:04.070 --> 10:05.120
No one's ever done that for me!

10:05.120 --> 10:06.090
Come on, Nutkin.

10:06.090 --> 10:06.790
Let's go.

10:10.680 --> 10:13.110
[CHATTERING]

10:14.080 --> 10:15.700
Is that everyone?

10:15.700 --> 10:16.400
OK.

10:16.400 --> 10:17.710
Let's go home.

10:17.710 --> 10:19.020
Wait!

10:19.020 --> 10:19.810
Where's Nutkin?

10:22.360 --> 10:24.020
My journal!

10:24.020 --> 10:25.340
He went back for it!

10:25.340 --> 10:30.300
I wonder how he managed to
get it without Old Brown seeing.

10:30.300 --> 10:31.240
Run!

10:31.240 --> 10:34.070
Give me back that book!

10:34.070 --> 10:37.020
I can't believe you went
back and got the journal!

10:37.020 --> 10:40.290
You put your tail on the
line and saved my life.

10:40.290 --> 10:41.670
Just my way of saying
thank you-- ouch!

10:41.670 --> 10:42.370
[MUSIC]

10:42.370 --> 10:44.190
(SINGING) Run, rabbit, run.

10:44.190 --> 10:47.170
Run like you've
never run before.

10:47.170 --> 10:49.160
Gotcha!

10:49.160 --> 10:51.150
(SINGING) Run, rabbit, run.

10:51.150 --> 10:54.130
If he catches you, you're
done so run some more.

10:57.110 --> 11:01.840
Those feet are sounding so
close to you, what can you do?

11:01.840 --> 11:03.260
Oh, rabbit, run.

11:03.260 --> 11:04.210
That's it!

11:04.210 --> 11:06.110
Give me my dad's journal.

11:06.110 --> 11:07.430
Whap!

11:07.430 --> 11:08.130
Oof!

11:11.250 --> 11:14.070
Aw, tailfeathers!

11:14.070 --> 11:18.000
You haven't heard the last
of this, Peter Rabbit!

11:18.000 --> 11:20.490
[CHEERING]

11:22.980 --> 11:28.320
It's good to have you
back, but I think I'd better

11:28.320 --> 11:29.520
keep you a little closer.

11:37.320 --> 11:38.820
[HOOTING OUTSIDE]

11:40.220 --> 11:40.920
[THEME MUSIC]

11:40.920 --> 11:46.020
(SINGING) Peter
Rabbit, Peter Rabbit.

11:52.020 --> 11:58.070
Peter Rabbit, Peter
Rabbit, Peter Rabbit.
